    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Appetite Suppressant Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Do appetite suppressant gummies actually work?</summary><p>Glucomannan reduced body weight by 0.8kg over 5 weeks in a meta-analysis of 9 RCTs (with calorie-controlled diet). 5-HTP reduced caloric intake by 38% in one study. Chromium provides modest craving reduction. No gummy produces weight loss without concurrent calorie reduction.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is glucomannan?</summary><p>Konjac root fiber that absorbs 50x its weight in water. Expands in the stomach to trigger stretch receptor satiety signals. EU-approved health claim for weight loss at 3g/day before meals with water.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>When should I take appetite suppressant gummies?</summary><p>30-60 minutes before meals with at least 8oz of water. This allows fiber to expand before food arrives. Take before the 1-2 meals where you overeat most. Never take glucomannan dry — esophageal blockage risk.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Are appetite suppressant gummies safe?</summary><p>Fiber-based: safe with adequate water. Main risks: esophageal blockage without water, GI discomfort when starting. 5-HTP: do NOT combine with antidepressants. Chromium: safe but may interact with diabetes medications. Avoid during pregnancy.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much weight can I lose?</summary><p>Glucomannan studies show ~0.8kg (1.8 lbs) over 5 weeks vs placebo. Real value is making calorie restriction sustainable by reducing hunger. A 500-calorie daily deficit produces ~1 lb/week fat loss. Gummies help maintain the deficit.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take these with other supplements?</summary><p>Separate fiber gummies from medications by 1-2 hours (fiber reduces absorption). Do not combine 5-HTP with antidepressants. Chromium may interact with diabetes medications. Safe with most vitamins and probiotics when timing is separated.</p></details>

